<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-1020] OCaml compiler generates invalid OCaml</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1020</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are a couple of bugs in the current thrift that cause invalid OCaml to be generated.  One problem is that floats can be written without a decimal point.  The other is that the copy type in the mli file is wrong.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The attached patch fixes both of the issues.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
