                            <comment id="12969825" author="bryanduxbury" created="Thu, 9 Dec 2010 17:32:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Why does this patch add a &quot;.0&quot; even when the constant is already a double? Wouldn&apos;t that result in multiple decimal places?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12970113" author="richardlow" created="Fri, 10 Dec 2010 10:01:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, I messed up.  As it was, out &amp;lt;&amp;lt; value-&amp;gt;get_doub)e() would not append a &quot;.0&quot; if the double was in fact an integer, but would otherwise.  The updated patch fixes this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12970976" author="bryanduxbury" created="Mon, 13 Dec 2010 19:18:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I just committed this. Thanks for the patch, Richard!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
